\f2\i0 \cf2 A Fractal Framework of Biblical Revelation\
\
\'93The testimony of Jesus is the spirit of prophecy.\'94 (Revelation 19:10)\
\
The Petals of Prophecy is a fractal biblical framework for understanding how divine revelation unfolds in progressive layers\'97like the blossoming of a flower. Each prophetic word in Scripture forms part of a composite whole, spiraling outward from Genesis to Revelation, each layer expanding but never contradicting the truths beneath.\
\
Solomon\'92s poetic wisdom, Isaiah\'92s messianic clarity, Ezekiel\'92s symbolic depth, and John\'92s apocalyptic vision all spiral together as petals on the same prophetic flower, pointing to the unfolding of Christ in every age.\
\
I. The Seed Core: Prophecy Rooted in the First Word\
\
At the center of the Petals of Prophecy lies the Seed of the Word itself:\
	\'95	Genesis 1:3: \'93Let there be light.\'94\
	\'95	Genesis 3:15: \'93The Seed of the woman shall crush the serpent\'92s head.\'94\
\
The Root Principle:\
	\'95	All prophecy originates in God\'92s self-revelation in creation.\
	\'95	Prophecy is not prediction but truthful revelation about the present with future fruit.\
\
Prophecy is the unveiling of eternal truth hidden in time.\
\
