IX. Practical Application: How to Read Scripture Through the Petals of Prophecy\
	1.	Look for Layers:\
	\'95	Prophecy echoes in patterns, not isolated events.\
	2.	Trace the Bloom:\
	\'95	From Genesis to Revelation, the flower expands and completes.\
	3.	Focus on Christ:\
	\'95	All prophecy points to Jesus as the final fulfillment.\
\
X. Conclusion: Prophecy as a Living Word\
\
The Petals of Prophecy reveal that all Scripture is a single unfolding revelation:\
	\'95	The Seed: God\'92s first Word.\
	\'95	The Bloom: Christ\'92s fulfillment.\
	\'95	The Full Flower: The new creation yet to come.\
\
Prophecy is not obscure predictions but the art of divine revelation, calling the soul to see both the now and the not yet through the Word Made Flesh.\
